[2026-03-31T10:27:45.208422+00:00] QUERY: what is the difference between vector search and BM25
RAW OUTPUT:
Vector search and BM25 are different approaches to information retrieval. Vector search is an approximate nearest neighbor (ANN) search technique that finds the k most similar vectors to a query vector, whereas BM25 is a traditional ranking algorithm that uses term frequencies and document frequencies to rank documents [1]. Vector search is specifically designed for high-dimensional embedding vectors, whereas BM25 is a general-purpose ranking algorithm [1].
